                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/11545: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="32" xml:id="d482fn32">Repeated in telegram No. 391 for the
                        information of the Embassy in China.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-12-09T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 9, 1937—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>335. Your 609, December 9, 5 p.m. While no objection is perceived to your
                    reminding the Foreign Office of the assurances repeatedly <pb facs="0403"
                        n="395" xml:id="pg_395"/> given with regard to safeguarding lives and
                    property of non-combatants, the Department considers it inadvisable as no
                    Americans are known to have been injured for you to request that an
                    investigation be made or to urge that those responsible be severely dealt
                        with.<note n="33" xml:id="d482fn33">The Ambassador in Japan in telegram No.
                        610, December 10, 11 a.m., reported no action was taken, but that “we will
                        look for an early opportunity to remind the Foreign Office of assurances
                        given regarding safety of lives and property.” (793.94/11555)</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
